(Description)
Write a function to find the longest common prefix string amongst an array of strings.
If there is no common prefix, return an empty string "".

--- Solution ---
class Solution {
    public String longestCommonPrefix(String[] strs) {
        if (strs == null) {
            return "";
        }

        String prefix = strs[0];

        for (int i = 1; i < strs.length; i++) {
            String current = strs[i];

            while (current.indexOf(prefix) != 0) {
                prefix = prefix.substring(0, prefix.length() - 1);

                if (prefix.isEmpty()) {
                    return "";
                }
            }
        }

        return prefix;
    }
}

--- Approach ---
# Key Concepts
Nested loop
Outer loop: searching the words in the given String array from second to last.
Inner loop: searching the common prefix throughout the comparsion between figured prefix and another word from outer loop.

# Point 1
I reminded how to use the indexOf(), and that saved my code efficency.
